Anonymous Fri 17 Nov 2023 15:53:52 No.61186746 Report

>>61184731
>soulless
I know this word gets thrown around a lot, but sovl is a real element. When SDS posts a new image, it's like Christmas morning! Everybody runs over to admire the image, crack jokes about it or just ask him questions. It doesn't happen every day, or every week even, and so the scarcity of the image makes us want it more.
But if an AI could shit out angular SDS-style images all the time, I would just get bored, consider them non-canon and wait for Dimsum to tripcode for the good shit.
Artists get to make every stroke in the image to support an overarching mood/theme, and it's so cool that such an emotion was even thought about. You can zoom in on the image and see where the artist crossed lines, got sloppy or tired when doing shading, or approximated a soft edge in a unique way. There's a whole struggle in every image that you can observe once you examine individual lines/strokes. It's personal. It goes for every half-decent artist out there.
When AI creates those details, it's because the prompt + random seed + math said that's where details should go. Why would I zoom in on a waifur image just to see how math works?
